---
// Drift-gate-blocks-swap demo — the single most important interaction
// on the landing. An animated "terminal" shows `c3p use dev` being
// refused because the user has uncommitted edits to
// `.claude/settings.json`, then suggests `c3p drift` and `git status`.
//
// Implementation rules:
//   - Pure CSS animation. No JS, so it never blocks LCP (F-1).
//   - Static markup means screen readers read the final state in order.
//   - `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` collapses every duration to
//     0.01ms via the global rule in `tokens.css` / `global.css`, which
//     naturally lands the demo on its final "moment of refusal" frame
//     (F-4).
//   - The terminal is decorative (the headline carries the message);
//     `aria-hidden="true"` keeps assistive tech from narrating the
//     ASCII while still letting visual users feel the animation. The
//     accessible summary lives in a sibling `.sr-only` paragraph so
//     the value prop is conveyed identically to all users.
---
<figure class="drift-demo">
  <p class="sr-only">
    Demonstration: running <code>c3p use dev</code> is refused because
    <code>.claude/settings.json</code> has uncommitted edits. C3P prints a
    refusal and tells you to commit, stash, or run <code>c3p drift</code>.
  </p>

  <div class="drift-demo__terminal" aria-hidden="true" role="presentation">
    <div class="drift-demo__chrome">
      <span class="drift-demo__dot drift-demo__dot--r"></span>
      <span class="drift-demo__dot drift-demo__dot--y"></span>
      <span class="drift-demo__dot drift-demo__dot--g"></span>
      <span class="drift-demo__title">~/your-project</span>
    </div>

    <pre class="drift-demo__pane"><span class="drift-demo__line drift-demo__line--prompt"
><span class="drift-demo__sigil">$</span> <span class="drift-demo__type"
>c3p use dev</span><span class="drift-demo__caret">█</span></span>
<span class="drift-demo__line drift-demo__line--blank"> </span>
<span class="drift-demo__line drift-demo__line--err"
><span class="drift-demo__badge">refused</span> uncommitted edits in <span class="drift-demo__path">.claude/settings.json</span></span>
<span class="drift-demo__line drift-demo__line--hint"
>  swapping now would <em>silently</em> overwrite your local changes.</span>
<span class="drift-demo__line drift-demo__line--blank"> </span>
<span class="drift-demo__line drift-demo__line--hint"
>  next: <span class="drift-demo__cmd">c3p drift</span> &middot; <span class="drift-demo__cmd">git status</span></span></pre>
  </div>

  <figcaption class="drift-demo__caption">
    The drift gate refuses unsafe swaps so your uncommitted work survives.
  </figcaption>
</figure>

<style>
  .drift-demo {
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  .drift-demo__terminal {
    background: var(--color-bg-elevated);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
    overflow: hidden;
    /* Reserve a sane min-height so the surrounding layout doesn't pop
       between the empty pane (frame 0) and the populated pane (frame
       N). Keeps LCP stable. */
    min-height: 14rem;
  }

  .drift-demo__chrome {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-2);
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4);
    background: var(--color-bg-surface);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .drift-demo__dot {
    width: 0.65rem;
    height: 0.65rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: inline-block;
  }
  .drift-demo__dot--r { background: #ef4444; }
  .drift-demo__dot--y { background: #f59e0b; }
  .drift-demo__dot--g { background: #10b981; }

  .drift-demo__title {
    margin-left: var(--space-3);
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--type-scale-1);
  }

  .drift-demo__pane {
    margin: 0;
    padding: var(--space-5);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--type-scale-2);
    line-height: var(--type-leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    /* Allow long lines to wrap on narrow viewports. */
    white-space: pre-wrap;
    word-break: break-word;
  }

  .drift-demo__line {
    display: block;
    /* Each line fades in at its own delay; final state is fully visible
       so reduced-motion (which collapses durations) lands on the
       refusal frame correctly. */
    opacity: 0;
    animation:
      drift-fade-in var(--motion-duration-md) var(--motion-easing-decel) forwards;
  }

  .drift-demo__line--prompt   { animation-delay: 100ms; }
  /* Skip the blank spacer at index 1 (it animates with no visual effect). */
  .drift-demo__line--err      { animation-delay: 1700ms; }
  .drift-demo__line--hint:nth-of-type(4) { animation-delay: 1900ms; }
  .drift-demo__line--hint:nth-of-type(6) { animation-delay: 2200ms; }
  .drift-demo__line--blank    { opacity: 1; animation: none; }

  .drift-demo__sigil {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-right: var(--space-2);
  }

  /* Typewriter effect on the command — animate `width` from 0 to its
     content length, hiding the overflow. `ch` units track monospace
     character width naturally. */
  .drift-demo__type {
    display: inline-block;
    overflow: hidden;
    white-space: nowrap;
    vertical-align: bottom;
    width: 0;
    animation: drift-type 1100ms steps(11, end) 200ms forwards;
  }

  .drift-demo__caret {
    display: inline-block;
    width: 0.6ch;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    animation: drift-blink 900ms steps(2, jump-none) infinite 1400ms;
  }

  .drift-demo__badge {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0 var(--space-2);
    margin-right: var(--space-2);
    background: var(--color-danger);
    color: var(--color-bg-primary);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: var(--type-scale-1);
    letter-spacing: var(--type-tracking-wide);
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .drift-demo__path,
  .drift-demo__cmd {
    color: var(--color-warn);
  }

  .drift-demo__line--err {
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }

  .drift-demo__line--hint {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .drift-demo__caption {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: var(--type-scale-2);
    text-align: center;
  }

  @keyframes drift-fade-in {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(2px); }
    to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  }

  @keyframes drift-type {
    from { width: 0; }
    to   { width: 11ch; }
  }

  @keyframes drift-blink {
    0%, 100% { opacity: 1; }
    50%      { opacity: 0; }
  }

  /* Reduced motion: belt-and-braces. Globals already collapse durations,
     but we explicitly land the typewriter on full-width and stop the
     caret from blinking so the final frame is unambiguously a refusal. */
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .drift-demo__line { opacity: 1; }
    .drift-demo__type { width: 11ch; }
    .drift-demo__caret { animation: none; opacity: 0; }
  }
</style>
